. We demonstrate that the exhalation and\ninhalation air flow dynamics have a significant impact on the stochastic\nfiltering of IAs by the face masks. Furthermore, we show that the fit of the\nface mask of the infected person can highly impact the infection probability.\nWe conclude that the proposed MC model may contribute a valuable assessment\ntool to fight the spread of SARS-CoV-2 as it encompasses the randomness of the\ntransmission process and enables comprehensive risk analysis beyond statistical\naverages.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Apr 2021 13:40:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 1 May 2021 14:03:11 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 16 Jan 2023 13:50:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
